ABUJA – The Nigeria Governors’ Forum (NGF) on Tuesday congratulated the winner of the just concluded gubernatorial election in Osun State, Senator Ademola Adeleke. Governor Kayode Fayemi Governor of Ekiti State, and Chairman, Nigeria Governors’ Forum, in a congratulatory letter dated 18th July, 2022, stated that the NGF wishes the Governor-elect success as he takes up the challenges that await his exalted office. The NGF assured him they look forward to working with Adeleke and assured him of the organisation’s commitment to providing outstanding services in line with global best practices. “The Nigeria Governors’ Forum (NGF) wishes to congratulate the Osun State Governor-elect, His Excellency, Senator Ademola Adeleke, on your victory at the just concluded election. “The NGF is a non-partisan platform of all 36 democratically elected State Governors of the Federal Republic of Nigeria irrespective of political affiliations. “At the Forum, all Governors are served equally and respectfully. “The NGF wishes you success as you take up the challenges that await you in your exalted office. “The Forum Secretariat assures Your Excellency of its full support as you embark on this new journey towards elevating your state to a higher level. POLL “We look forward to working with you and assure you of our commitment to provide outstanding services in line with global best practices and hope that you will in turn trust the Forum’s machinery to at all times provide you professional technical and administrative support. “We wish you God’s guidance, strength, direction and the wisdom to deliver on your mandate to your people. Your Excellency, once again, congratulations and welcome to the Nigeria Governors’ Forum,” he said.